ctrl + shift + v => show md file view



1. Headers

# H1 - Largest Heading
## H2 - Second Largest Heading
### H3 - Third Largest Heading
#### H4
##### H5
###### H6 - Smallest Heading



2. Paragraphs

This is a paragraph. Markdown will automatically handle text wrapping.



3. Bold and Italics

Bold: Use double asterisks ** or double underscores __.
Italics: Use single asterisks * or single underscores _.
Bold and Italics: Use triple asterisks ***.


**This is bold text**  
*This is italicized text*  
***This is bold and italicized text***



4. Lists

Ordered Lists (Numbered)
1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item

Unordered Lists (Bullet points)
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Sub-item 1
  - Sub-item 2



5. Links

Create hyperlinks using [text](URL).
[Visit GitHub](https://github.com)




6. Images

Add images using the same syntax as links, but with an exclamation mark ! at the beginning: ![alt text](image URL).
![Markdown Logo](https://markdown-here.com/img/icon256.png)

local image
![My Local Image](./path-to-image/myimage.png)



7. Code Blocks

Inline code
This is `inline code`.

Code blocks
i) ```javascript
function greet() {
  console.log("Hello, World!");
}
```
ii) > This is a blockquote. Itâ€™s used for quotations.



9. Tables

Tables are created using pipes | and hyphens -. Align text using colons :.

| Header 1 | Header 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Row 1    | Data     |
| Row 2    | Data     |



